ther confused with or derived from   Trumble  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Bulman","meanings":["English (northern): occupational name for a keeper of a bull or bulls, from Middle English <i>bule</i> ‘bull’ + <i>man</i> ‘man’. In Ireland, this has been a common name in Cork since the 17th century.","In some cases possibly also an Americanized form of German <b>Bullmann</b> (see   Bullman  )."]},{"name":"Trumble","meanings":["English (Lancashire and Yorkshire): from a Middle English personal name <i>T(h)rumbald</i> (Old English <i>Trumbeald</i>, from <i>trum</i> ‘strong’ + <i>beald</i> ‘brave’).","Scottish (of Norman origin): habitational name from Le Tremblay (Eure).","Scottish: variant of   Turnbull  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   John  , also used quite frequently in the English-speaking world. In Northern Ireland it is sometimes found as a variant of   Ewan ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Baron John Turnbull of Minto was born about 1345, in Minto, Roxburghshire, Scotland, his father, Sir John Turnbull, was 31 and his mother, Lady Mary Haliburton, was 29. He had at least 1 son with Diana Stewart Erskine. He died on 31 July 1423, in Cravant, Loiret, Centre-Val de Loire, France, at the age of 79."},"et":{"about 1345–31 July 1423":"umbes 1345–31. juuli 1423","1332–1381":"1332–1381","1345–1423":"1345–1423","1347–1381":"1347–1381","1361–1410":"1361–1410","1382–1440":"1382–1440","1315–1355":"1315–1355","1317–1347":"1317–1347","1440":"1440","1340":"1340","1361":"1361","1382":"1382","1381":"1381","1315":"1315","1347":"1347","1423":"1423","1345":"1345","1355":"1355","1410":"1410","31 July 1423":"31. juuli 1423","1332":"1332","about 1345":"umbes 1345","1317":"1317","Minto, Roxburghshire, Scotland":"Minto, Roxburghshire, Scotland","Battle of Cravant, France":"Cravant, Loiret, Centre-Val de Loire, Prantsusmaa","Scotland":"Scotland",", , , Scotland":"Šo